com.thinkaurelius.titan.core

Interface TitanVertexQuery<Q extends TitanVertexQuery<Q>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseVertexQuery<Q>, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Query, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.VertexQuery
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VertexCentricQueryBuilder

    public interface TitanVertexQuery<Q extends TitanVertexQuery<Q>>
extends BaseVertexQuery<Q>, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.VertexQuery
    A TitanVertexQuery is a VertexQuery executed for a single vertex.

    Calling TitanVertex.query() builds such a query against the vertex this method is called on. This query builder provides the methods to specify which indicent edges or properties to query for.

    Author:
    Matthias Bröcheler (http://www.matthiasb.com)
    See Also:
    BaseVertexQuery

      • has

        Q has(String type,
    Object value)
        Description copied from interface: BaseVertexQuery
        Query only for edges or properties that have an incident property or unidirected edge matching the given value.

        If type is a property key, then the query is restricted to edges or properties having an incident property matching this key-value pair. If type is an edge label, then it is expected that this label is unidirected (EdgeLabel.isUnidirected() and the query is restricted to edges or properties having an incident unidirectional edge pointing to the value which is expected to be a TitanVertex.

        Specified by:
